### Is there an existing issue for this?

- [x] I have searched the existing issues

### Describe the bug

The below code deadlocks in 13.3, but worked in 13.1. 

This seems to be because `WithEnvironment` for containers is now being called before endpoints are allocated.  This issue doesn't seem to affect executables.  I suspect it's container tunnel related.

 (I haven't tested 13.2 - my current assumption is this is caused by enabling container tunnel by default in 13.3)

### Expected Behavior

_No response_

### Steps To Reproduce

```cs
builder.AddContainer("container", "container", ".")
    .WithHttpEndpoint(targetPort: 8080)
    .WithEnvironment(async ctx =>
    {
        Console.WriteLine("WITHENV");
        var endpoint = ((IResourceWithEndpoints)ctx.Resource).GetEndpoint("http");
        var url = await endpoint.GetValueAsync();
        ctx.EnvironmentVariables["URL"] = url;
    });
```

### Exceptions (if any)

_No response_

### .NET Version info

_No response_

### Anything else?

Further evidence can be seen with the below code:

In 13.1.0+8a4db1775c3fbae1c602022b636299cb04971fde, outputs

```
On Initialise
Executable OnBeforeResourceStarted
Container OnBeforeResourceStarted
Executable WithEnvironment
Container WithEnvironment
```

In 13.3.0-preview.1.26153.13+bd9fc4f59591806b227e8602b32d1f4d9045b86b however, the same code is giving me

```
Container WithEnvironment
On Initialise
Container WithEnvironment
Container OnBeforeResourceStarted
Executable OnBeforeResourceStarted
Container WithEnvironment
Executable WithEnvironment
```

The last four events are the same, but in 13.3, there are now two extra calls to `WithEnvironment`, one of which occurs very early in the application lifecycle.  There now being multiple calls to the same `WithEnvironment` method is also a surprise that could cause other breakages.

```cs
builder.AddContainer("container", "container", ".")
    .WithEnvironment(ctx =>
    {
        Console.WriteLine("Container WithEnvironment");
        return Task.CompletedTask;
    })
    .OnBeforeResourceStarted((_, _, _) =>
    {
        Console.WriteLine("Container OnBeforeResourceStarted");
        return Task.CompletedTask;
    })
    ;

builder.AddExecutable("exe", "exe", ".")
    .WithEnvironment(ctx =>
    {
        Console.WriteLine("Executable WithEnvironment");
        return Task.CompletedTask;
    })
    .OnBeforeResourceStarted((_, _, _) =>
    {
        Console.WriteLine("Executable OnBeforeResourceStarted");
        return Task.CompletedTask;
    })
    ;

var fake = builder.AddResource(new FakeResource("fake"))
    .OnInitializeResource((_, _, _) =>
    {
        Console.WriteLine("On Initialise");
        return Task.CompletedTask;
    });

class FakeResource(string name) : Resource(name)
{

}
```
